column1: Welcome to the master tracking spreadsheet for the Students Learn Students Vote Coalition! This tracker is used to coordinate our efforts in enrolling campuses in NSLVE, getting them to publish their reports on their websites, and getting them to write/implement action plans to increase student voting engagement. In order to make best use of this spreadsheet, please double check that the schools where you work are accurate and updated. To best adminster this tracker, we've set the sharing setting as view-only for Coalition Partners. To display certain data, you can create a temporary filter view. This allows you to apply certain filters without changing the view for anyone else. To create one, go to "Data>Create a temporary filter view." Be sure that you have the second row selected, as that is where the data is sorted. For example, you could create a list of your campuses that have submitted a 2018 Action Plan by removing the "(Blanks)" value in column M and removing the "(Blanks)" value on your organization's column. If you have any questions about this tracker or you need to update your school listings/have an NSLVE report publishing link to post, please email info@slsvcoalition.org Thanks!
